General Information

Contains Calcium, which may assist in the prevention of osteoporosis when dietary intake is inadequate
Contains Vitamins D & K to support the development and maintenance of strong healthy bones
Contains nutrients which support healthy bone mineralisation and density

Calcium is involved in the development and maintenance of the bones and teeth.
A diet that is deficient in Calcium can lead to osteoporosis in later life.
Adequate dietary Calcium throughout life is required to maximise bone.
Vitamins D and K also support healthy bone mineral density.

Warnings

Always read the label; take only as directed. Vitamin supplements should not replace a balanced diet.

Formulated without:
Gluten, wheat, dairy products, egg, artificial flavours, artificial sweeteners or preservatives.

Directions

Take 3 tablets daily with food or as directed by your healthcare professional.
